      <h1 class="title">Meet Jessie</h1>
      <h3 class="sub-title">~ Birth Doula | Postpartum Doula  ~</h3>
      <p>
        Jessie’s journey to becoming a doula began when she was just a child. At the age of seven, Jessie was present to watch as her brother was born at home. Her mother, a midwife and doula, educated Jessie about what was to be expected and then she witnessed as her baby brother entered the world in her parents bedroom. The memories of that day are still vivid and bring warm feelings of love and family connectedness whenever she thinks about it.
As Jessie got older, she worked with children in many different settings, got her Bachelor's Degree in Social Work, a license in Early Childhood Education and then worked as a preschool teacher for nine years. During her time as a preschool teacher, Jessie gained a deeper understanding of infants and how we as adults can nurture their development. During that time,
Jessie also realized how families were not getting the early support and education they needed to feel successful. With her passion to support families, she left her preschool career to become a birth and postpartum doula. Jessie believes that when given the right amount of support, love and education, families can have more meaningful and positive birth and postpartum experiences.
      </p>
